@EndNode

@Node "Note"

    The strings:
    - "Error xx in line xx"
    - "Command returned xx/xx"

    Are not translated, because they are in  rexxsyslib.libraryRexx()
    and RX and so can't easly be patched.

    Only the italian and français catalogs in this distribution.

    Note about Developers/RexxPathError.cd:
    - the MSG_XXX are the ARexx error messages
      they are limited to 82 chars due to the internal method used by
      ARexx to store error messages.
    - the RXP_MSG_XXX are the RexxPatchError strings:
      - RXP_MSG_CXDES is the description strings for the commodity
      - RXP_MSG_OVER is the string showed in a requester when the program
                     tries to exit, but someone set-funtioned
                     rexxsyslib.library/ErrorMsg()
@EndNode


